The Independent Police Investigative Directorate arrested six police officers in Boksburg on Wednesday. The Nigerian consulate was present during the arrests. #eNCA #dstv403  JOHANNESBURG - Six police officers from the Boksburg North police station have been arrested. The Independent Police Investigative Directorate made the arrests on Wednesday.  #eNCA speaks to IPID spokesperson Lizzy Suping. #DStv403  Two of the officers face charges of copper theft and defeating the ends of justice. Four are facing charges of assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm and defeating the ends of justice. They allegedly beat a Nigerian man into a coma. The Nigerian consulate was present during the arrests. 